# GitHub CODEOWNERS — auto-assign reviews per path
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Order matters: later patterns override earlier ones.
# Combined with branch protection's "Require review from Code Owners",
# any PR touching these paths requires the owner's approval.

# Default: everything is owned by the repo admin
*                            @edupazogle

# ─── Frontend / design system ───
/app/                        @edupazogle
/components/                 @edupazogle
/design-proposal/            @edupazogle
/lib/client/                 @edupazogle
*.css                        @edupazogle
*.tsx                        @edupazogle

# ─── Backend gateway (Python) ───
/gateway/                    @edupazogle
/lib/server/                 @edupazogle

# ─── Database & infra (high blast radius) ───
/db/migrations/              @edupazogle
/infra/                      @edupazogle
/flows/                      @edupazogle

# ─── CI/CD & agent config (highest blast radius — tightest gate) ───
/.github/                    @edupazogle
/.github/workflows/          @edupazogle
/.github/agents/             @edupazogle
/.github/CODEOWNERS          @edupazogle

# ─── Docs ───
/docs/                       @edupazogle
